heme of his work character, the public sphere, culture, democracy, the city, labor, social work, writing, pragmatism, and ethics and thus provide an important reference work in the German-language reception of Sennett.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aCharakter. 4aDemokratie. 4aEthik. 4aGegenwartsgesellschaft. 4aGesellschaft. 4aHandwerk. 4aKritik. 4aKultur des Kapitalismus. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aLiteratur. 4aPragmatismus. 4aRaum. 4aSoziale Arbeit. 4aSozialität. 4aSozialphilosophie. 4aSoziologie. 4aSoziologische Theorie. 4aStadt. 4aÖffentlichkeit. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aCharakter.  aCity.  aContemporary Society.  aCritique.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture of Capitalism.  aDemocracy.  aEthics.  aHandcraft.  aLiterature.  aPragmatism.  aPublic Sphere.  aSocial Philosophy.  aSocial Relations.  aSocial Work.  aSociety.  aSociological Theory.  aSociology.  aSpace.1 aAugust, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEckardt, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroßmaß, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamla, Jörn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLorenz, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLorenz, Stephan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRosa, Hartmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScheele, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScherr, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlette, Magnus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeinstock, Alexander, econtributor.